com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.step

Interface TableSDK


  • public interface TableSDK
    TableSDK represents the SDK's view of a Data Studio table, and allows certain operations to be performed on them. Tables are contained within Datastore objects that represent Data Studio datastores i.e. file or JDBC. It is intended for use by process flow steps that need to create or append new data from other sources.

      • getDisplayName

        String getDisplayName()
        Gets the display name for the table. Tables can be renamed, so it is advisable to reference them by Id or external name instead.
        Returns:

      • getExternalName

        String getExternalName()
        Gets the external name for the table. If the table is a file it is the filename, if the table is a database table it will be the name of the table. This name cannot be changed.
        Returns:
        String external name

      • getType

        String getType()
        Gets the type of the table. Only applies to file tables and returns the extension name of the file. If a database table it returns null.
        Returns:
        String file type

      • clearCachedData

        boolean clearCachedData(long userId)
        Clears the cached data for the table. Data will be recached when the data is next viewed in Data Studio. Will return false if not successful.
        Parameters:
        userId - - obtained in the SDK using the getUserId() function
        Returns:
        true if successful
